data.title: Andrew Ross - 2005-06 - Men's Golf
data.meta_description: Andrew Ross - 2004-05 : Named Golf Coaches Association All-America Scholar at the conclusion of the 2004-05 season, just the second ASU golfer ever to receive that
data.text:
2004-05 : Named Golf Coaches Association All-America Scholar at the conclusion of the 2004-05 season, just the second ASU golfer ever to receive that recognition ... led the team in stroke average, at 74.58 ... best individual finish was a tie for 10th in the UALR/First Tee Collegiate ... low round of 69 came in the Â‘49’er Collegiate Classic, hosted by Charlotte ... had five top-25 finishes for the season.

2003-04 : Played in 29 rounds ... fourth on the team in stroke average, at 76.10 ... best round of 68 came in the Nestle’ Purina Classic ... best three-round total of 216 also came in the Nestle’ tourney ... best individual finish was 17th in the SBC Championship ... finished tied for 19th in the Squire Creek Intercollegiate, his best finish of the fall.

2002-03 : Ended fourth on the team in stroke average at 75.40 as a freshman ... best round of 69 came in the Fall Beach Classic ... best three round total of 214 came in the same Fall Beach Classic ... posted two top-25 finishes, including ending tied for 16th in the Fall Beach Classic.

High School : Named Golfer of the Year as a junior and senior ... made the honor roll four straight years in high school ... four-year letterman on golf team at Hamilton-Wentworth District School.

Miscellaneous : Born 3-7-83 in Hamilton, Ontario ... son of Stephen Ross ... enjoys hockey ... business administration major ... member of the Dean’s and President’s List every semester at ASU.
